Facebook has hired former Lib Dem leader and former Deputy Prime Minister Nick Clegg. The ex-Sheffield Hallam MP is expected to move to Silicon Valley to lead the social network's global affairs and communications team, according to the Financial Times. ALSO READ:

Instagram, Facebook 'fuelling' modern day slavery, baby trafficking He'll replace Elliot Schrage, who recently announced he would be leaving after a decade at the tech giant. Mr Clegg reportedly took the job after months of 'wooing' by Mark Zuckerberg. The FT reported he would be given a leading role in shaping the firm's strategy.